      "tocHtml": "<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#Download-Image\">Download Image</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Create-Boot-Device\">Create Boot Device</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Installation\">Installation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Update-Sources-List\">Update Sources List</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Configure-Openbox\">Configure Openbox</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Install-Asian-Fonts\">Install Asian Fonts</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Enable-Sound\">Enable Sound</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Configure-Dev-Tools\">Configure Dev Tools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#References\">References</a></li>\n</ol>",
      "articleHtml": "<h2 id=\"Download-Image\">Download Image<a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#Download-Image\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-link\"></i></a></h2>\n<p>Download <a href=\"https://cdimage.debian.org/debian-cd/current/amd64/iso-cd/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Debian image</a>, let we choose the net-install ISO since we don&#x27;t need any heavy desktop enviroment e.g. KDE, GNOME, etc... .</p>\n<h2 id=\"Create-Boot-Device\">Create Boot Device<a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#Create-Boot-Device\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-link\"></i></a></h2>\n<p>There are a ton of tools which can burn ISO to a USB or CD, simply follow the instruction and create the boot device.</p>\n<h2 id=\"Installation\">Installation<a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#Installation\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-link\"></i></a></h2>\n<p>Plug the USB into your computer reboot and following the instruction to complete the installation. Remember to use a different partition for <strong>/home</strong> which is helpful for reinstallation in the future.</p>\n<h2 id=\"Update-Sources-List\">Update Sources List<a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#Update-Sources-List\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-link\"></i></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.debian.org/SourcesList\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://wiki.debian.org/SourcesList</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://backports.debian.org/Instructions/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://backports.debian.org/Instructions/</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"Configure-Openbox\">Configure Openbox<a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#Configure-Openbox\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-link\"></i></a></h2>\n<pre><code>sudo apt install xinit openbox menu xfce4-terminal\nehoc &quot;exec openbox-session&quot; &gt;&gt; ~/.xinitrc\necho &quot;startx&quot; &gt;&gt; ~/.bash_profile\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"Install-Asian-Fonts\">Install Asian Fonts<a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#Install-Asian-Fonts\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-link\"></i></a></h2>\n<pre><code>sudo apt install fonts-arphic-ukai fonts-arphic-uming fonts-ipafont-mincho fonts-ipafont-gothic fonts-unfonts-core\nsudo fc-cache -fv\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"Enable-Sound\">Enable Sound<a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#Enable-Sound\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-link\"></i></a></h2>\n<pre><code>sudo install alsa-utils\namixer set Master 100% unmute\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"Configure-Dev-Tools\">Configure Dev Tools<a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#Configure-Dev-Tools\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-link\"></i></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.debian.org/Java\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://wiki.debian.org/Java</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.debian.org/VisualStudioCode\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://wiki.debian.org/VisualStudioCode</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.debian.org/Chromium\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://wiki.debian.org/Chromium</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"References\">References<a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#References\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-link\"></i></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.debian.org/Openbox\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://wiki.debian.org/Openbox</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/149368\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/149368</a></li>\n</ul>"
